**Changed by:** Rebase of TQC/anyon citation amendment onto v1.3.0 (Class C / M55 Reality Offload)
**Verification:** verified-local — markdownlint clean; both TQC and M55/Class C content present

### What changed
- Added a new "Real Citations Reusable for Topological Quantum Computation (TQC) Mechanisms" section with 5 real cited papers (Kitaev 2003, Nayak et al. 2008, Nakamura et al. 2020, Xu et al. 2024, Microsoft Majorana 1 2025)
- Added "Key TQC Facts for M-Series Writers" section: Fibonacci vs. Ising anyon distinction, fusion rules, Hilbert-space dimension, universality vs. Clifford-only results, topological protection (Wall 11) formula
- Added TQC/anyon WebSearch terms to the detailed Step 1 (Kitaev, Nayak, Nakamura, Fibonacci-processor searches)
- Added new Failed Attempts row: confusing Ising/Majorana anyons with Fibonacci anyons for universal TQC
- Added M44 (anyon/topological braiding fabric) to the Verified On table
