## v1.1.0 (2026-06-01)

**Changed by:** M16 asymptotic-safety substrate mechanism design (Myrmidon swarm physics agent)
**Verification:** unverified — theoretical framework extended with new mechanism data point

### What changed
- Added M16 asymptotic-safety wall-by-wall analysis to Results & Parameters
- Extended Failed Attempts table with one new entry (2D CFT conflation)
- Added new insight: Wall 5 (sign problem) is specifically defeated by CDT/Lorentzian approaches (novel finding vs AdS/CFT defeat mechanism)
- Updated Capability Score Rubric with M16 scores
- Added NP-1/NP-2/NP-3 postulate taxonomy to new-physics postulate naming convention

### Why
M16 design session revealed that the sign problem (Wall 5) can be defeated via a different mechanism than the AdS/CFT path: Lorentzian CDT causal ordering eliminates the oscillatory Euclidean sign problem directly, independent of large-N limits. This is a distinct defeat mechanism worth documenting. Also: the 14-wall framework was applied for the second time, now with two distinct mechanism types (holographic boundary vs RG-flow substrate), allowing cross-mechanism comparison data.

